The main stream of the Yangtze River realizes full coverage of the water green comprehensive service area-Xinhuanet Xinhua Agency, Wuhan, December 11 th(Reporter Wang Xian) Chongqing City Fuling Water Green Comprehensive Service Area was completed and put into operation on schedule on the 10th. This is the second water green comprehensive service area officially put into operation in the upper reaches of the Yangtze River after Luzhou Water Green Comprehensive Service Area in Sichuan Province was put into operation on the 8th. So far, the water green comprehensive service area has covered the upper, middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River. Qiu Jianhua, deputy director of the Yangtze River Navigation Administration of the Ministry of Transport, said that before this, Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Anhui,Jiangsu and other provinces have built and operated 10 water green comprehensive service areas in the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River, which have been recognized by the majority of sailors and played an important role in promoting the high-quality development of Yangtze River shipping. The full coverage of water green comprehensive service areas is another milestone in the construction of green shipping on the Yangtze River. The capacity of receiving pollutants from ships and shipping services on the Yangtze River has been significantly improved. According to introduction, the water green comprehensive service area is an important facility to provide all-round production and living services for the vast number of ships and crew members, and to help the vast number of crew members solve the problem of "anxious and anxious". The two water green comprehensive service areas on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River, which have been completed and put into operation this time, integrate living services, production services and government affairs services, take green environmental protection as the theme, and feature ship maintenance and ship emergency rescue services, so as to realize "one berthing, multiple services" for ships in the port.It will make the crew who sail in the Yangtze River all the year round work more efficiently and live more conveniently.
